DANVILLE, Vt., Oct. 31â€”Dr. Ernest Little, dean emeritus of the Rutgers University. College of Pharmacy and the first president of the American Foundation for Pharmaceutical Education, died here yesterday at his home. He was 85 years old.

Dr. Little graduated with Phi Beta Kappa honors from the University of Rochester in, 1911, and continued his graduate work in chemistry there and at Columbia University, where he received his Ph.D. in 1924.

He joined the Rutgers faculty in 1918 and was named a professor in 1924 and dean of pharmacy two years later. He retired as dean in 1946 and as professor in 1954.

Dr. Little was the moving spirit in the establishment in 1942 of the American Foundation for Pharmaceutical Education, which provides fellowships for advanced study in the field.